    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR adds Python-side runtime support for Moss-VL in SRT.\r\n\r\nThe changes include:\r\n- add `MossVLForConditionalGeneration` model support\r\n- add a Moss-VL multimodal processor\r\n- register Moss-VL conversation template and model-type matching\r\n- pass Moss-VL-specific multimodal metadata through schedule/forward paths\r\n- support cross-attention custom masks in the FlashInfer prefill path\r\n- update tokenizer/model runner flow to initialize Moss-VL multimodal inputs correctly\r\n\r\n## Details\r\n\r\nMain updates:\r\n- add `python/sglang/srt/models/moss_vl.py`\r\n- add `python/sglang/srt/multimodal/processors/moss_vl.py`\r\n- register Moss-VL in model config and conversation template matching\r\n- extend multimodal scheduling inputs with Moss-VL-specific fields such as:\r\n  - `vision_position_ids`\r\n  - `media_nums_per_sample`\r\n  - `visible_frame_counts`\r\n- allow model-specific forward-batch preparation before attention metadata init\r\n- propagate cross-attention custom masks into FlashInfer prefill metadata\r\n\r\n\r\n",
